cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.NA, cs.DM, cs.GT 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper presents algorithms for computing bottleneck paths and shortest paths for all possible flow amounts, which are fundamental problems in graph theory and algorithms. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry): The paper deals with directed graphs and edge capacities, which are common topics in computational geometry. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper involves computing shortest paths and bottleneck paths, which are numerical problems that can be solved using numerical methods. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The paper presents combinatorial algorithms for solving the SSSP-AF and APSP-AF problems, which are discrete optimization problems. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): The paper discusses real life applications of the bottleneck paths and shortest paths problems, which can be related to game theory and decision making.
